        <c02 level="item" id="d1e197">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>to 
                  <persname>James Kirke Paulding</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1841 October 1</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Requests additional poems and biographical
                  information to be included in a proposed new
                  collection to be titled 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Poets and Poetry of America</bibref>.
                  ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e222">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>to 
                  <persname>George Roberts</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1841 November 1</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>1 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Recommends that 
                  <persname>George B. Leiber</persname>become the new
                  agent in 
                  <geogname>Philadelphia</geogname>for the 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">[Boston] Notion</bibref>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e253">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>to 
                  <persname>Edwin Percy Whipple</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">[ca. 1846] November 15</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>3 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Discusses current literary projects and requests
                  assistance in obtaining pamphlet by 
                  <persname>[Orestes] Brownson</persname>and in writing
                  a brief sketch on 
                  <persname>[Francis] Bowen</persname>including
                  Coleridgism, Emersonism, transcendentalism--"a
                  retrospect of philosophy in the 
                  <geogname>United States</geogname>. " Also mentions 
                  <persname>[William Gilmore] Simms</persname>, 
                  <persname>Edgar Allan Poe</persname>and 
                  <persname>[Joel Tyler] Headley</persname>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e294">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>to 
                  <persname>[Spencer Fullerton]
                  Baird</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">n.d.</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>1 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Concerns summer travels of friends and himself.
                  Writes scathingly of "the learned Blacksmith" ( 
                  <persname>Elilu Burritt</persname>), 
                  <persname>William Hewitts</persname>and 
                  <persname>Mary Hewitt</persname>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
